# Commit Message Style Guide for `{{ repo_name }}`

Analysis based on {{ commits_analyzed }} recent commits
from the `{{ repo_name }}` repository.

## Core Principles

Write commit messages that are technically precise yet
casual in tone. Use abbreviations and informal language
while maintaining clarity about what changed and why.

## Subject Line Format

### Length and Structure
- Target: ~50 chars (hard-max of 67).
- Use backticks around code elements
  ({{ backtick_pct }}% of commits)
{%- if colon_usage_pct > 10 %}
- {{ colon_usage_pct }}% use colon notation
  (`module.file:` prefix or `: ` separator)
{%- endif %}
- End with `?` for uncertain changes (rare)
- End with `!` for important changes (rare)

